**Job Title:** 
 Senior Quality Program Manager




**Location:** 
 Sweden - Danderyd




 Trimble is an exciting, entrepreneurial company, with a history of exceptional growth coupled with a disciplined and strategic focus on being the best. While GPS is at our core, we have grown beyond this technology to embrace other sophisticated positioning technologies and, in doing so; we are changing the way the world works.




**Job Responsibilities**
 This on-site Sr Quality Program Manager, based in Danderyd, Sweden, is responsible for supporting the development and production of high-precision optical instruments. In this role, you'll play a vital role in helping our team succeed by ensuring the highest quality standards throughout the production process for our precision optics.




 You will develop and implement strategic initiatives to meet the highest quality standards across all products and processes, from conception to manufacturing. A critical focus will be analyzing field failures and warranty returns to drive improvements.




* Implement standardized processes and templates for corporate regulatory, internal, and supplier audit programs. Drive process improvements and integrate Quality Compliance requirements;
* Establish and oversee programs to monitor and improve Quality System effectiveness. Manage the internal audit schedule, ensuring adherence and providing status updates;
* Develop a certification program for internal auditors. Lead and coach the audit team on regulatory, quality, and system effectiveness audits for facilities and suppliers;
* Ensure compliance with quality standards through meticulous attention to detail and a focus on standardization, documentation, and continuous improvement;
* Plan and conduct annual audits, incorporating quality metrics, audit results, industry trends, and regulatory changes;
* Support the CAPA process by collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure effective investigation, action plan implementation, and monitoring;
* Work with Compliance and cross-functional teams to ensure products meet global environmental regulations and customer requirements;
* Enhance product quality and reliability by analyzing field failures, implementing corrective actions, and reducing warranty costs to boost customer satisfaction;
* Participate in warranty cost reduction programs and promote continuous improvement through adherence to manufacturing quality plans.


**Skills & Experience Required**
* Bachelor’s degree in a technical field (preferably Engineering); 5-7 years of experience, with a focus on corrective and preventive actions;
* Hands-on Quality Assurance experience in a production environment;
* Proficient in ISO 9000 and ISO 14000 standards;
* Advanced proficiency in Swedish and English;
* Strong skills in process improvement and investigative tools (e.g., Cause and Effect Diagrams, Trend Analysis, Control Charts);
* Ability to prioritize multiple tasks and preferred experience in Risk Assessment, Reliability Engineering, and Product/Process Validation;
* Willingness to travel 5-20%.


**About Trimble**
 Dedicated to the world’s tomorrow, Trimble is a technology company delivering solutions that enable our customers to work in new ways to measure, build, grow and move goods for a better quality of life. Core technologies in positioning, modeling, connectivity and data analytics connect the digital and physical worlds to improve productivity, quality, safety, transparency and sustainability. From purpose-built products and enterprise lifecycle solutions to industry cloud services, Trimble is transforming critical industries such as construction, geospatial, agriculture and transportation to power an interconnected world of work. For more information about Trimble (NASDAQ: TRMB), visit:
 *www.trimble.com*
****Trimble’s Inclusiveness Commitment****
 We believe in celebrating our differences. That is why our diversity is our strength. To us, that means actively participating in opportunities to be inclusive. Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion have guided our current success while also moving our desire to improve. We actively seek to add members to our community who represent our customers and the places we live and work.




 We have programs in place to make sure our people are seen, heard, and welcomed and most importantly that they know they belong, no matter who they are or where they are coming from.




